<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - SPEEDOMETER AND TACHOMETER SENSORS - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the new sensor by turning into the housing until it bottoms out against the
                speedometer gear or flywheel ring gear.
                <emph type="underscr">Back off one (1) TURN.</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the lock nut using two wrenches to keep the sensor from turning while tightening the
                lock nut. Torque to 15 ft-lbs. (20 N&#8226; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-connect the sensor connector to the wiring harness connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Test drive the vehicle to test the speedometer. Run the engine to test the tachometer.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
